    <div class="crowd-tip"><strong>Best time:</strong> Weekday mornings are the quietest — the beach is used primarily by local runners, dog walkers, and visitors exploring the museum area. Saturday evening around midnight is the busiest time of week during the midnight sun season, when groups gather to watch the sun on the horizon. The beach has no physical capacity limit as an open outdoor space, but the viewing area with the best westward sightline is a relatively narrow stretch — arrive early on summer weekend nights for position.</div>
