      <div class="fq-a">Swimming is possible in summer. Water temperatures in the Tromsø strait reach approximately 14–17°C in July and August. The beach has sandy and pebbled sections suitable for wading. There is no lifeguard service. Cold-water swimmers use the beach year-round.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Is Telegrafbukta good for midnight sun viewing?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Yes. The beach has a clear westward orientation across the Tromsø strait, giving an unobstructed view of the sun sitting on the horizon at midnight during the midnight sun season (approximately 20 May to 22 July). It is the best free ground-level viewpoint in Tromsø for this purpose, without the cable car fare required for Fjellheisen summit.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What facilities are at Telegrafbukta?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Telegrafbukta is an open public outdoor space with no paid facilities — no lifeguard, café, or changing rooms at the beach itself. The Tromsø University Museum is approximately 300 m north and its Café Rotunden is the nearest indoor facility. Walking and cycling paths run along the adjacent coastline.</div>
